I/O Extended events help developers from around the world take part in the I/O experience.

I/O brings together developers from around the globe for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and the first look at Google‚Äôs latest developer products.

Google I/O is an annual software developer-focused conference held by Google in San Francisco, California. Google I/O features highly technical, in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open web technologies such as Android, Chrome, Chrome OS, Google APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more.

events.description:
Kickstarting the Google Developer Community with NEXT ‚Äô19 Extended Skopje! üöÄüá≤üá∞

We are excited to bring together the developer community to be a part of the NEXT ‚Äô19 experience. This event will cover talks on Data Analytics, Artificial Intelligence, and Machine learning.

* We have a limited number of seats, 80 seats, so the event seating is organized on a first come first serve basis.

Agenda:

18:00 - 18:15 - Registration
18:15 - 19:00 - Icebreakers and Welcome
19:00 - 19:15 - Video Call: Kyle Paul, Program Manager, Developer Ecosystems at Google
19:15 ‚Äì 19:45 - Live Stream: ML Options for Mobile Developers (Next '19)
19:45 ‚Äì 20:30 - David Simeonovski and Simona Ivanova, Kaggle: "A great way to get into data science."
20:30- 20:45 - Raffle and prizes!
20:45 ‚Äì 21:30 - Networking - beer and pizza time!

More info about speakers:

David Simeonovski:

David is a data scientist working at Web Factory, Pendulibrium team. His interests include algorithms, data mining, computer vision, and reinforcement learning. He is a regular participant in programming competitions and hackathons, with relatively high success. Last year, he was tied for first place at the student programming competition Code Fu. In February he was a part of the best Macedonian team at the Google Hash Code competition which qualified for the finals in Dublin. He was also part of the Pendulibrium team which finished in the top 2% at the Kaggle Santander Prediction competition in April.

Simona Ivanova:
Bachelor of Computer Science and currently working as an AI Engineer at Web Factory, Pendulibrium team. Interested in machine learning, research, and AI. In the last 3 years, she has worked on a handful of machine learning projects that deal with various topics. Always willing to step outside her comfort zone and work on cutting edge technologies, eager and willing to constantly add to her knowledge base and skills. Last year she participated at NASA Space Apps Challenge as a mentor and recently as part of team Pendulibrium was placed among top 2% on a Kaggle competition thus winning a silver medal.

upcoming.name: Build fast with Flutter
upcoming.description:
Join this Flutter Meetup to get to know more about #Flutter and how to build beautiful native apps in record time with a single codebase.üê¶

// Agenda

Meetup (Open session):

19:00 - 19:15 PM - Registrations
19:15 - 19:40 PM - Icebreakers
19:40 - 20:10 - Redux in Flutter: An Introduction - Jeroen Meijer, Admin, and Head of GitHub @ Flutter Community

Brief info about the talk:
In software development, small projects are quite different from large apps. As the scope gets bigger and functionality is added, quick solutions that worked before might create bugs later, state management can become complex and logic and UI changes are difficult to implement as requirements change. In this talk, Jay will explain how a state management pattern called ‚ÄòRedux‚Äô can help you keep your app can become easier to build, more readable and more quickly expandable.

20:10 - 20:40 PM - Social Change with Flutter - MojVozduh Demo, Gorjan Jovanovski, Software Engineer @Booking
20:40 - 21:00 PM - Raffle time
21:00 - 22:00 PM - Pizza, Beer, and Networking

---------------------------------------

Workshop - "Social Change with Flutter" (Closed session):
18:00 - 19:00 - Gorjan Jovanovski will work with participants to build components of Moj Vozduh with Flutter, and teach them how easy it is to create an app for iOS and Android with the same code.

Application for the workshop is separate. Apply here -> bit.ly/Flutter-Workshop

More info about Flutter: https://flutter.dev/
